  <bioghist id="aspace_d55125ca02a2d5593692d576418e2368">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Ithaca Airways was founded by Herbert M. Peters in Ithaca, Tompkins County, New York. It later became Ithaca Flying Service Inc.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_7b80ca4667afb63c26948d148ec972e7">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Records include correspondence, 1928-29, and Ithaca Airways miscellany; financial records including cancelled checks, deposit slips, notes, mortgages, cancelled stock certificates, and invoices, 1928-40, also ledger books, cashbooks, checkbooks, receipt books, and bank books for the Ithaca Airways Corporation and the Ithaca Flying Service, 1928-42, also one daybook of the Cornell Flying Club, 1935-36; pilot information including training forms, maps, notes, exams, pamphlets, an atlas, and logbooks, 1929-41; and Herbert M. Peters' personal papers including financial records and miscellany, 1927-42; and Dorothy B. Peters' records as treasurer for Girl Scout Camp Comstock 1939, and School District 16, Town of Ulysses, 1939.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_3fb576fe52aced86d93c88d36ce7b253">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Ithaca Airways records, #3169. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
